&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project Coordinator&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Empowering the Future of Mobility: Join Powerdot’s Innovative Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Charging your car should feel as natural as charging your phone. That’s the future we’re building: a network of EV chargers where life happens.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We don’t just install chargers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We accelerate sustainable mobility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We obsess over partnerships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We grow relentlessly:our network, our partners, ourselves.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’re here, you’re probably not looking for “just a job.” Neither are we. 😎 We’re driven by impact, and always looking for people who thrive on turning bold ideas into reality. If that sounds like you, you’ll feel at home here.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for people who:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;See challenges as puzzles, not problems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Thrive in fast-growing, high-energy environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Want to shape the future of mobility, not just watch it unfold.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Powerdot, you’ll get &lt;strong&gt;freedom&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;ownership&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;responsibility&lt;/strong&gt;. The space to experiment. The chance to scale your ideas. And a team that’s always pushing the edge of what’s possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your mission is to coordinate the rollout of EV charging stations projects within the time and budget framework. You will manage several projects simultaneously and, together with partners, implement the project according to a variety of criteria such as budget, resources, risks, and milestones.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Each project involves several stakeholders, whom you will coordinate to ensure the successful completion of the project. These include the partner (owner of the property where the station is to be installed), electricity grid operators (Ores, Fluvius, Resa, Sibelga, etc.), engineering firms, installation partners, local authorities, etc.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your role will be dynamic, with a multitude of functions, primarily divided into two strategic areas:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Installations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will coordinate the rollout of EV charging stations across multiple sites.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Management of installation partners: daily monitoring of our multiple projects with our installers, and identification and resolution of bottlenecks in our installation chain.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mobilization of internal and external resources (installation partners, service providers, suppliers, Ores, Fluvius, Sibelga, Power Dot technicians) adequate to deploy our stations as quickly as possible while ensuring quality, safety and attractiveness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordination of the delivery of the charging stations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You may be required to travel to perform technical visits or commissioning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Streamlining internal processes to cut deployment timelines and project expenditures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow up on the operation of the charging stations in service to build a strong relationship with our key partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Business up-selling to get additional sites signed within a major account&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow-up of the files before signature: direct relationship with the Sales team to carry out technical visits on site, interviews, and implementation plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re seeking a driven, organized professional who thrives in fast-paced environments and loves taking ownership from day one. At this stage, we prioritize attitude over aptitude, we are looking for a mindset, not just a resume.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wh

&lt;p&gt;Charging your car should be as easy as charging your smartphone. And so for that to happen, chargers need to be available where people naturally spend their days.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our mission is as simple as it is ambitious: &lt;strong&gt;Accelerate Sustainable Mobility&lt;/strong&gt; by investing in, installing, and operating EV chargers with a cutting-edge business model. We help businesses find the right charging solutions for their customers. Today, we&#39;ve partnered with over 1,200 businesses across Portugal, Spain, France, Belgium, Luxembourg, and Poland, with more than 2,200 contracted locations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are, first, &lt;strong&gt;Partner Obsessed&lt;/strong&gt; 🤝 — creating bespoke solutions to better serve our partners&#39; customers. We love the challenge of making EV charging simpler, readily available, and integrated with diverse retail and service experiences 💡. And we are all about &lt;strong&gt;growing&lt;/strong&gt; 📈 — expanding our network, our partners&#39; businesses, and the professional development of our team, all while driving the EV ecosystem forward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We seek empowered top performers who share our mission and values, and who are ready to think disruptively and join our exciting journey. 🚀&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🚀 About this Role&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;As an &lt;strong&gt;Project Manager &lt;/strong&gt;specializing in EV charging hub deployment, you&#39;ll play a vital role in delivering seamless, turnkey charging solutions to our customers across Portugal &amp;amp; Spain. Your mission is to drive efficient, high-quality deployment of charging stations — ensuring every project is delivered on time, on budget, and to the highest safety standards, while keeping installation pipelines flowing without friction. This dynamic position is central to Powerdot&#39;s operations and growth in Portugal &amp;amp; Spain.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How You&#39;ll Shape Our Story:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Your day-to-day will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;text-start &quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project Management&lt;/strong&gt; — overseeing daily progress across multiple projects with installation and engineering partners, identifying and resolving bottlenecks in the installation pipeline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;text-start &quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Resource Coordination&lt;/strong&gt; — working closely with internal and external stakeholders — including installers, contractors, suppliers, and energy distributors — to ensure efficient deployment of charging stations with a focus on quality, safety, and speed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;text-start &quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technician Supervision&lt;/strong&gt; — organizing and guiding internal technicians for technical site visits, commissioning, and activation of charging stations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;text-start &quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Logistics Management&lt;/strong&gt; — ensuring timely delivery of charging equipment to project sites.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;text-start &quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CAPEX Control&lt;/strong&gt; — managing investment per location by negotiating with subcontractors and ensuring projects align with budgets and timelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;text-start &quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Emergency Response&lt;/strong&gt; — conducting site visits or performing commissioning tasks personally when urgent situations arise.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
